\title{[relations](jms-00I7) in program specification}
\date{2024-01-17}
\contributor{marcelofiore}
\author{jonmsterling}
\taxon{example}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{In the simplest terms, a specification of a program is a [relation](jms-00I7) that describes the possible input/output pairs that can occur. For example, the specification that a given program compute the square root is captured by the [relation](jms-00I7) #{\mathsf{sq} \colon \mathbb{R}_{\geq 0} \relto \mathbb{R}} given by pairs \prn{x,y} such that #{x = y^2}.}